# Fit regression model:
score_model <- lm(score ~ bty_avg, data = evals_ch6)
# Get regression table:
get_regression_table(score_model)

Learning Check 11.1 (10 minutes)

Using age as the explanatory variable and teaching score as the outcome variable, use the get_regression_points() function to get the observed values, fitted values, and residuals for all 463 instructors. Perform a residual analysis and look for any systematic patterns in the residuals. Ideally, there should be little to no pattern.

# Fit regression model:
score_model1 <- lm(score ~ age, data = evals_ch6)
# Get regression table:
get_regression_table(score_model1)
## # A tibble: 2 x 7
##   term      estimate std_error statistic p_value lower_ci upper_ci
##   <chr>        <dbl>     <dbl>     <dbl>   <dbl>    <dbl>    <dbl>
## 1 intercept    4.46      0.127     35.2    0        4.21     4.71 
## 2 age         -0.006     0.003     -2.31   0.021   -0.011   -0.001
regression_points1 <- get_regression_points(score_model1)
ggplot(regression_points1, aes(x = residual)) +
  geom_histogram(binwidth = 0.25, color = "white") +
  labs(x = "Residual")

ggplot(regression_points1, aes(x = age, y = score)) +
  geom_point() +
  labs(x = "Age", y = "Teaching Score",   title = "Relationship between teaching and beauty scores") +
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", se = FALSE)

Bootstrapping the slope

bootstrap_distn_slope <- evals_ch6 %>% 
  specify(formula = score ~ bty_avg) %>%
  generate(reps = 1000, type = "bootstrap") %>% 
  calculate(stat = "slope")
visualize(bootstrap_distn_slope)

95% CI for bootstrapped slope

percentile_ci <- bootstrap_distn_slope %>% 
  get_confidence_interval(type = "percentile", level = 0.95)
percentile_ci
## # A tibble: 1 x 2
##   `2.5%` `97.5%`
##    <dbl>   <dbl>
## 1 0.0327  0.0983
observed_slope <- evals %>% 
  specify(score ~ bty_avg) %>% 
  calculate(stat = "slope")
observed_slope
## # A tibble: 1 x 1
##     stat
##    <dbl>
## 1 0.0666
se_ci <- bootstrap_distn_slope %>% 
  get_ci(level = 0.95, type = "se", point_estimate = observed_slope)
se_ci
## # A tibble: 1 x 2
##    lower upper
##    <dbl> <dbl>
## 1 0.0329 0.100

Comparing CIs

visualize(bootstrap_distn_slope) + 
  shade_confidence_interval(endpoints = percentile_ci, fill = NULL, 
                            color = "red") + 
  shade_confidence_interval(endpoints = se_ci, fill = NULL, 
                            color = "blue") +
  shade_confidence_interval(endpoints = c(0.035, 0.099), fill = NULL, 
                            color = "darkgreen")

Hypothesis tests around the slope

null_distn_slope <- evals %>% 
  specify(score ~ bty_avg) %>%
  hypothesize(null = "independence") %>% 
  generate(reps = 1000, type = "permute") %>% 
  calculate(stat = "slope")
visualize(null_distn_slope)

visualize(null_distn_slope) + 
  shade_p_value(obs_stat = observed_slope, direction = "both")

null_distn_slope %>% 
  get_p_value(obs_stat = observed_slope, direction = "both")
## # A tibble: 1 x 1
##   p_value
##     <dbl>
## 1       0

Learning Check 11.2 (10 minutes)

Repeat the inference above but this time for the correlation coefficient instead of the slope. Note the implementation of stat = correlation in the calculate() function of the infer package.

null_distn_correlation <- evals %>%
  specify(score ~ bty_avg) %>%
  hypothesize(null = "independence") %>%
  generate(reps = 1000, type = "permute") %>%
  calculate(stat = "correlation")
visualize(null_distn_correlation)

observed_correlation <- evals %>%
  specify(score ~ bty_avg) %>%
  calculate(stat = "correlation")
observed_correlation
## # A tibble: 1 x 1
##    stat
##   <dbl>
## 1 0.187
visualize(null_distn_correlation) +
  shade_p_value(obs_stat = observed_correlation, direction = "both")

null_distn_correlation %>%
  get_p_value(obs_stat = observed_correlation, direction = "both")
